# Tailwind v4

CSS-first config. No `tailwind.config.ts`. Tokens live in `app/globals.css` under `@theme` directives.

## Importing

```css
/* app/globals.css */
@import "tailwindcss";

@theme {
  --color-bg: #0a0a0b; /* page bg, near-black */
  --color-surface: #16161a; /* card bg */
  --color-surface-2: #1f1f25; /* elevated card bg */
  --color-border: #2a2a32;
  --color-fg: #f5f5f0; /* primary text */
  --color-fg-muted: #a8a8a0; /* secondary text */
  --color-accent: #d4af37; /* signature gold */
  --color-accent-hover: #e6c14a;
  --color-danger: #ef4444;
  --color-success: #22c55e;
  /* ... etc ... */
  --font-sans: "Inter", system-ui, sans-serif;
  --font-display: "Playfair Display", Georgia, serif;
}
```

## No arbitrary hex in components

```tsx
// ❌
<div className="bg-[#d4af37]">

// ✅
<div className="bg-accent">
```

A reviewer rejects any `bg-[#...]`, `text-[#...]`, etc. that isn't a deliberate one-off (annotated with a comment).

## Design tokens vs utility classes

Use Tailwind utilities for layout (`flex`, `grid`, `gap-*`, `p-*`). Use token-backed semantic classes for colors, typography, radius:

- `bg-bg`, `bg-surface`, `bg-surface-2`
- `text-fg`, `text-fg-muted`, `text-accent`
- `border-border`
- `font-sans`, `font-display`

## Dark-first

KCLUB is dark-first (ADR-001 visual decision in B02 prompts; codified in SPEC follow-up). There is no light mode at MVP. Don't add `dark:` variants until light mode is in scope.

## Components

shadcn/ui copied into `src/components/ui/`. Edit freely — they are not imported from a remote registry. Updates from upstream are manual cherry-picks.

```tsx
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";

<Button variant="default" size="lg">{t("cta")}</Button>
```

Variants live in `cva()` calls inside each component file. To add a variant, edit the file, don't wrap externally.

## Accessibility

- Min tap target: 44×44px. Use `min-h-11 min-w-11` (11 * 4 = 44).
- Focus rings: shadcn defaults are fine. Don't `outline-none` without replacing the focus indicator.
- Color contrast: every text-on-background combo passes WCAG 2.2 AA (4.5:1 normal, 3:1 large). The token palette above is pre-checked; arbitrary colors are not.

